{
  "texts": [
    "20, is a commonly used pooling method in deep learning.",
    "It extracts the second-order relationships between features by computing the outer product of two input feature maps.",
    "This method is able to better capture the spatial relative positions and interactions between features.",
    "21 proposed three new pooling methods: hybrid pooling, gate pooling, and tree pooling.",
    "Hybrid pooling combines different pooling functions and dynamically selects which pooling operation to apply to each pixel based on the specific requirements."
  ]
}